    <h2 id="setup"><i class="fa-solid fa-tools"></i> Getting Setup</h2>

    <p class="text-warning"> <em>Please have these steps' setup before the contribution weekend!</em></p>

    <ol>
        <li><strong>Create an account on <a href="https://drupal.org/user/register" class="ext">Drupal.org</a></strong> if you do not yet have one.</li>
        <li>
            <strong>Join the conversation Drupal's <a href="https://www.drupal.org/slack" class="ext">Slack</a> groups</strong>

            <p>Add <a href="http://drupalslack.herokuapp.com">Drupal Slack</a> and <a href="https://vandug.herokuapp.com/">Van DUG</a> groups.

            <p>Join the
                <code>#drupal-pnw</code> and
                <code>#drupal-contribute</code> slack channels.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
    <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-hiking"></i> Choose your own adventure:</h3>

    <details>
        <summary>Local Development Environment: DDEV</summary>
        <div class="details__content">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Install <a href="https://git-scm.com/downloads" class="ext">git</a></strong>.
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-link help" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#git" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="git">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-question fa-xl"></i>
                </button>
                <div id="git" class="collapse">
                    <p><a title="Free online git reference book" href="https://git-scm.com/book" class="ext">free online reference book</a></p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p><strong>Install <a href="https://ddev.readthedocs.io/en/stable/">DDEV</a>.</strong>
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-link help" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#dev-stack" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="dev-stack">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-question fa-xl"></i>
                    </button>
                </p>
                <div id="dev-stack" class="collapse">
                    <p>There are plenty more local development environments to choose from in the guide: <a href="https://www.drupal.org/docs/develop/local-server-setup" class="ext">Local server setup</a>. </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p><strong>Create a local D9 website:</strong>
                    <strong>Clone <a href="https://www.drupal.org/project/drupal/git-instructions" title="Drupal 9.x.x | drupal.org">Drupal 9</a> with git:</strong>

                </p>
                <pre><code>mkdir ~/Sites/d9
cd ~/Sites/d9
git clone https://git.drupalcode.org/project/drupal.git web
ddev config</code></pre>


            </li>
            <li><strong>Install Drupal and <em>you're ready to patch!</em></strong>

                    <p>From within the project directory</p>
                    <pre><code>ddev drush si standard</code></pre>

            </li>
        </ol>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Cloud Development Environment: DrupalPod</summary>
        <div class="details__content">This is great if you don't want to touch your machine(or can't) yet still want to
            code.
            <a href="https://github.com/shaal/DrupalPod">DrupalPod</a></div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Existing Development Environment: DYI</summary>
        <div class="details__content"><p>You already have your setup, great! Carry on...</p>
            <p>Have a peak at the <a href="https://www.drupal.org/docs/system-requirements">Drupal requirements</a> if
                you need to tweak your setup:
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>No Development Environment</summary>
        <div class="details__content">There are plenty of ways to contribute without setting up a development environment, from simplytest.me,
            editing documentation and helping triage and move issues, to editing files directly in Gitlab on
            drupal.org.</div>
    </details>

